A Toyota land cruiser registration no. KBV 983v was yesterday intercepted in Ng’ari village along Kirisia Forest ferrying 25 illegal immigrants believed to be from Eritrea to an unknown destination. 22 of them were arrested by police in collaboration with area chiefs and nyumba kumi officials and are now being held at Maralal Police Station awaiting to be arraigned in court, with three still at large. This and other stories from across the country. 